is\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American world champion at the distance was hoping become the first man since Usain Bolt at the Rio 2016 Games to secure both the 100 metres and 200 metres titles.\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 413, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999991106022651, \"rank\": 8.702834605601158e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Usain Bolt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\"}, {\"begin\": 509, \"end\": 512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9996049127072876, \"rank\": 0.0003952434484238683, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had managed to bounce back to win 100 metres gold at the2024 Olympics, but this time could not compensate for what was again the slowest reaction time of the pack.\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 744, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tebogo crossed in 19.46 for his first Olympic title and the United States' Kenny Bednarek snapped up silver.\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 806, \"end\": 819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996788094936562, \"rank\": 0.00014025401012129175, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"b